DifferenceLimiter (V. 5.x) (V. 6.x) (V. 7.x)
The output value is limited in its difference to the last input value. The maximum valid difference is LU, the
minimum valid difference is LD. Only for a sampling time of 1s this block behaves like a Gradient limiter. For
other sampling times this time has to be taken into account in setting the correct values for LU and LD.
