When you change the While Iterator block to do-while operation, the IC (initial condition) input disappears from
the While Iterator block. The important distinction between the while and do-while modes of the While Iterator
block is that the do-while mode runs the While subsystem at least once. In while mode, the While subsystem
may not run its blocks at all depending on the value of the initial condition (IC).
